<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 3:37AM CDT  by NWS Dallas-Fort Worth</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Hopkins and
southwestern Delta Counties through 415 AM CDT...
At 336 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Cumby, moving east at 55 mph across Hopkins County.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Sulphur Springs, Cumby, Como, Cooper Lake, Cooper Lake State Park,
Lake Sulphur Springs, Klondike, Pine Forest, Tira, New Birthright,
Ridgeway, Nelta, Peerless, Dike, Martin Springs, Weaver, Flora and
Cornersville.
This includes Interstate 30 between mile markers 110 and 142.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
